[{"id":27140,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Acetone as substrate and methanol in stoichiometric amount","Propanal as substrate and methanol in excess","Propanal as substrate and methanol in stoichiometric amount","<p>Acetone as substrate and methanol in excess</p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Acetal is form from the reaction of aldehyde with excess of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9c894103-33d1-4e7d-97e5-851a80a590e4-image29.png\" /></p><p>Formation of an acetal occurs when the hydroxyl group of a hemiacetal becomes protonated and is lost as water. The carbocation that is produced is then rapidly attacked by a molecule of alcohol. Loss of the proton from the attached alcohol gives the acetal.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27144,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"220\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2483b613-08e0-46ac-a291-66c40310abd2-image.png\" width=\"337\" /></p><p><img height=\"220\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8cfed5ea-fdcd-409d-839c-fce99f947476-image.png\" width=\"336\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/95cfd0e8-14e7-4279-90ca-18a57b754a57-image.png\" style=\"width: 459px; height: 156px;\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"215\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a8196df-a5c6-4a45-b91e-ca4bc274f8c1-image.png\" width=\"336\" /></p><p><img height=\"215\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/174d423d-a729-4b75-8234-251e6ce7973a-image.png\" width=\"337\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"159\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed34ba5c-0a79-4803-bf3c-cc7c1d90d76d-image.png\" width=\"463\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>This is an intramolecular aldol condensation reaction.</p><p><img height=\"100\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/72600d96-01f8-44e0-b1ee-9b2a393deeef-image.png\" width=\"424\" /></p><p><img height=\"137\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/360c20ab-6cb3-4d9a-9617-0819d1e9e9ab-image.png\" width=\"379\" /></p><p><img height=\"107\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/903e68a9-d5ea-416a-b71f-85cdedcd5ff6-image.png\" width=\"450\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27065,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p>One optically active and one meso product</p>","Two optically inactive products","<p>Two optically active products</p>","<p>One optically inactive and one meso product</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The aldehyde group of glyceraldehyde reacts with hydrogen cyanide give cyanohydrin. Two isomers formed in the above step, because aldehyde is planar and changed to tetrahedral centre. On hydrolysis cyanide group convert to carboxylic acid. Upon reaction with nitric acid, the primary alcoholic group undergo oxidation to carboxylic acid group. One compound is meso compound, optically inactive and other compound is optically active.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f48911b1-bde7-4a74-bd9e-58b0452ed2ff.png\" style=\"width: 411px; height: 479px;\" />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27093,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>This reaction is an example of intra molecular Claisen condensation reaction.&nbsp;The mechanism of the Claisen condensation reaction proceeds with the removal of an alpha proton through the action of a strong base to result in the formation of an enolate ion.&nbsp;</p><p>This results the formation products as follows,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/03e6b3b6-d2c4-4655-8970-9e3e71778acb-image.png\" style=\"width: 324px; height: 150px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27058,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Stephen reaction","Etard reaction","Gatterman-koch reaction","Rosenmund reduction"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Gattermann – Koch reaction is used for the industrial production of benzaldehyde. </p><p>In Gattermann – Koch reaction, benzene is treated with carbon monoxide in the acidic medium in presence of anhydrous aluminium chloride to give benzaldehyde. In this reaction, anhydrous aluminium chloride works as a catalyst. It is an electrophilic substitution reaction.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aa7eeb78-cb04-4862-a172-6589570c1d9e.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 183px;\"/></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27022,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["B, C & E Only","A & D Only","A & E Only","A, B & E Only"],"answer":2,"solution":"The iodoform test is given by compounds containing the methyl ketone group ($CH_3CO-$) or alcohols that can be oxidized to methyl ketones ($CH_3CH(OH)-$).<br>A. Methanol ($CH_3OH$) does not give the test, while Ethanol ($CH_3CH_2OH$) gives a positive iodoform test because it contains the $CH_3CH(OH)-$ group. Thus, they can be differentiated.<br>B. Acetic acid ($CH_3COOH$) and Propanoic acid ($CH_3CH_2COOH$) both do not give the iodoform test. Carboxylic acids generally do not respond to this test. Thus, they cannot be differentiated.<br>C. Cyclohexene and cyclohexanone both do not give the iodoform test. Cyclohexanone lacks a methyl group adjacent to the carbonyl carbon. Thus, they cannot be differentiated.<br>D. Diethyl ether ($CH_3CH_2OCH_2CH_3$) and Pentan-3-one ($CH_3CH_2COCH_2CH_3$) both do not give the iodoform test. Thus, they cannot be differentiated.<br>E. Anisole ($C_6H_5OCH_3$) does not give the test, while Acetone ($CH_3COCH_3$) gives a positive iodoform test as it is a methyl ketone. Thus, they can be differentiated.<br>Therefore, iodoform test can differentiate pairs A and E.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27157,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9vrQtHyPcgFuIeUDt304GYS125KmGX-XZZs1OSMFkYQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/AgPKF3OaG7lX9EVvkXyfv0DPhWGbGrOjV0MB7v-J8fk.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/rpMQbqzjAiy9IcMbT5_bYAbvwYw-FGjtv8y8iT7J8Jw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/P4qgNkRI7z_iuFsS1dVvHjKeqRqGr9FBpCUV87i1xc0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Sodium borohydride reduces ketonic group to alcohol, but not the amide group and $\\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{C}$ double bond.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":27150,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"63\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/563b5f47-fef8-4eb5-b256-bfab3d880291-image.png\" width=\"262\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"64\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e4e25da9-2086-4207-9d53-16a955d9ed23-image.png\" width=\"282\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"65\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b1424272-617c-4976-88a6-2b36e8e2902d-image.png\" width=\"282\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"71\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2ea15da8-333e-4a22-b174-3f06780c308c-image.png\" width=\"274\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math> selectively reduces&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> group to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>CH</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>|</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>OH</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>&nbsp;and imine group to amine.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27128,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed465e2b-7cb4-4d41-8e86-07937c8f2c48-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 125px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/337991b7-57e9-4f11-b8e7-d1d43a27137c-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 84px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/83557426-e94d-4adc-89cc-b03e9b15afbb-image.png\" style=\"width: 238px; height: 82px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ee4f95f9-cd3b-4954-a095-7dbcacebe08e-image.png\" style=\"width: 181px; height: 122px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e9b6eed8-7c93-47c0-9a9d-2065c2d7673d-image.png\" style=\"width: 532px; height: 322px;\" /></p><p>Markovnikov&#39;s addition states that, in hydrohalogenation of an unsymmetrical alkene, the hydrogen atom in the hydrogen halide forms a bond with the doubly bonded carbon atom in the alkene, bearing the greater number of hydrogen atoms.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27041,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true","Both Statement I and Statement II are true"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{eq}}=2280$ is for HCHO\n$\\mathrm{k}_{\\text {eq }}=2000$ is for chloral\nBoth data is given in clayden and warren book. $\\mathrm{k}_{\\mathrm{eq}}>1$ because HCHO and chloral are more electrophilic.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27126,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["(I)-(Q), (II)-(R) and (III)-(P)","(I)-(P), (II)-(Q) and (III)-(R)","(I)-(R), (II)-(P) and (III)-(Q)","(I)-(R), (II)-(Q) and (III)-(P)"],"answer":2,"solution":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 500px;\">\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/52ab7133-1e59-45aa-bd63-284c92203f92-image.png\" style=\"width: 337px; height: 179px;\" /></td>\t\t\t<td>Gatterman-Koach reaction</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/610ade81-2f08-4913-9924-931e06413d64-image.png\" style=\"width: 366px; height: 164px;\" /> Reduction</td>\t\t\t<td>Stephan Reduction</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d6500930-58f2-4728-bf4e-5bd7e33f4c07-image.png\" style=\"width: 333px; height: 172px;\" /></td>\t\t\t<td>Rosenmund Reduction</td>\t\t</tr>\t</tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27075,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9476dad8-747d-4da5-b5d1-929d6fb88a78-9896610.PNG\" style=\"width: 178px; height: 150px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c7f0ce89-0fd4-4f25-aa77-576cd76372a2-9896610_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 169px; height: 150px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/590e4ec4-c998-4773-9a4c-1c901a31899b-9896610_2.PNG\" style=\"width: 183px; height: 150px;\" />&nbsp;","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fa2d0c77-ec0f-4f29-a8b4-820119c873dd-9896610_3.PNG\" style=\"width: 189px; height: 150px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Cyclohexylamine when treated with nitrous acid yields cyclohexanol.On treating cyclohexanol with PCC&nbsp;which is a mild oxidising agent and oxidises the alcohols into aldehyde (in case of primary alcohol) or ketones (in case of secondary alcohol) in the presence of dichloromethane results cyclohexanone. When cyclohexanone is heated with dilute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NaOH</mi></math>&nbsp;dehydration of aldol takes place by the removal of water molecules we get the final product.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b66380fe-0a65-4185-b44c-e963ad6052b6-13835c82-f123-4d20-9f4f-0bc5eaaf7924-9896610_4.PNG\" style=\"width: 577px; height: 112px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27039,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/VZSehJRgCBl4aN9pKRSJJ2cC8sQfqTKaWMaH7IUktPM.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_0Mg5vrayjPxJQFo8hQe-hNGW5qYsVxuXn8-1PcvrOo.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/OOs9dpK8I2FvqZM_7qQvXdIXNEIk5ho2HJNN4SKdwGA.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/JiY7RsoJKGSqINK8ovFrrwTDaZHM75luX5CBKYXYN_s.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/oRWOVwmFSwdJMWADhUamfOWJU9_CsvtUKCVK8ll5oL0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27084,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e1716037-93dd-4fe7-af25-714197ea13e1-9893508_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 169px; height: 150px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e2f2a6b4-9b5e-40a6-804a-27538e6b66fa-9893508_2.PNG\" style=\"width: 223px; height: 150px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5512e1c6-0b86-449b-a00f-edc4a80fe5b9-9893508_3.PNG\" style=\"width: 360px; height: 94px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8ee6e327-d804-4d00-ae15-3441476984fd-9893508_4.PNG\" style=\"width: 191px; height: 92px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The cross aldol reaction takes place between isobutyraldehyde and formaldehyde&nbsp;to&nbsp;get hydroxypivaldehyde. On reaction with hydrogen cyanide&nbsp;followed by hydrolysis produces the lactone product.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/048c981b-734c-466b-af6f-d4fa7f8efab3-9893508_5.PNG\" style=\"width: 497px; height: 242px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27136,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≈</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≈</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≈</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≈</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≈</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>d</mi><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mrow><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"></mi><mi>P</mi><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"></mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>  <br/><math><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>i</mi><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"></mi><mi>N</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>S</mi><mi>F</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"></mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>  <br/><math><msup><mrow><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>i</mi><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>N</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> <math><mi>N</mi><msup><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>S</mi><mi>F</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> <math><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>  <br/><math><msup><mrow><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>i</mi><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi>O</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> <math><mi>N</mi><msup><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>W</mi><mi>F</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> <math><msubsup><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi></mi><mtext> </mtext><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi></mi><mtext> </mtext><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>,</mo><mi></mi><msubsup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mi></mi><mtext> </mtext><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup></math> So, unpaired electron is <math><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"></mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>8</mn></msqrt><mi></mi><mi>B</mi><mi>M</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27174,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Ethyl methyl ketone","Isopropyl alcohol","$3-$Methyl$-2-$ butanone","Isobutyl alcohol"],"answer":3,"solution":"Iodoform is given by\n$1)$ methyl ketones $\\mathrm{R-CO-CH_3}$\n$2)$ alcohols of the type $\\mathrm{R-CH(OH) CH}_3$ where $\\mathrm{R}$ can be hydrogen also\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/LXkOgzScYmXRb7GtHP_vNSjasXnh5cIq_1kkl4wiz8w.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ymh-WLKuYnp4olJZJ8NR2ynKUjA7GPsrUeJFO_v-NNM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":27108,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Two","One","Four","Three"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f738a834-499f-4575-8246-5722ba3af377-image.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 90px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27154,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/76affbe4-1b28-44b4-89da-d90d2081cb8a-image.png\" style=\"width: 193px; height: 140px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25692c3d-5c17-4583-a1af-d658a2373284-image.png\" style=\"width: 235px; height: 158px;\" /></p>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/435b4c9e-4808-494b-84d2-4671d8123c45-image.png\" style=\"width: 223px; height: 159px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f03d0b1c-bda2-462b-9581-99b5a6f8f28a-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 142px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a0d98a4b-7c15-4b8c-9716-22406d74a070-image.png\" style=\"width: 223px; height: 159px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ccf579da-077a-46a6-8d55-61bab1332a44-image.png\" style=\"width: 122px; height: 83px;\" /></p><p>group gives 2,4-DNP test and&nbsp;iodoform test.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9176f350-c029-4b5c-926b-1c2e3be61ac6-image.png\" style=\"width: 125px; height: 110px;\" /></p><p>not in the plane of benzene so no dye test.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27156,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/516b9b2d-b807-4ba5-bced-c20e3f4a4da3-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 90px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bd01fd8b-697a-4849-96f4-3cb15a5baac9-image.png\" style=\"width: 196px; height: 87px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f5abf1ec-8904-4e86-9e82-26bd5b179289-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 90px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/99d02e46-68dc-4cdf-a969-1f25e85c1e25-image.png\" style=\"width: 183px; height: 117px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Initially aldehyde reacts with Grignard reagent to form a secondary alcohol.&nbsp; Which undergo nucleophilic substitution reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1c04260b-420e-4991-ae40-a9f7290b8f8c-image.png\" style=\"width: 819px; height: 137px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (16 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27092,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b00714d5-a6ef-417f-8f7b-d85917424518-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 104px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ee5a29e-2fd9-40df-8d07-409cdb803764-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 98px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/20e58c8d-1d4f-4fa0-bfcd-5da3b79c6f0f-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 87px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6efea129-5777-41ec-9a0e-e0420ff46bdc-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 86px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Cyanide on reduction with DIBAL-H gives aldehyde. Acid halide with rosenmund reduction reaction gives aldehyde. So, all these reaction&nbsp;are correct except benzyl alcohol with oxidation with strong oxidising agents sodium dichromate will give carboxylic acid not the aldehyde.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2aa1a864-8c40-4b24-b2c7-d25d55aac27f-20e58c8d-1d4f-4fa0-bfcd-5da3b79c6f0f-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 119px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27098,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> /acetic acid,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> /acetic anhydride,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>KMnO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mo>,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CO</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Anhyd</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>AlCl</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Toluene is oxidised to benzaldehyde in presence of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> /acetic anhydride,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p><p>Toluene is converted to&nbsp;benzylidene diacetate&nbsp;and&nbsp;hydrolysis reaction of benzylidene diacetate&nbsp;gives benzaldehyde.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9edbce60-686a-4097-85d4-4bea5da15ff4-image.png\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 175px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27033,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["5","4","3","2"],"answer":1,"solution":"Following will not give iodoform reaction/test.<br />(1) Butanal<br />(2) 2-Pentanone<br />(3) Pentanal<br />(4) 3-Pentanol","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27086,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f59531b4-2b76-4f78-88db-2a5d1da39482-image.png\" style=\"width: 252px; height: 70px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ac979fe6-4922-45b5-917f-ccecaa6baa7c-75a5f7d6-b036-4a97-9546-dd11225e947c-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 68px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e5960d99-87b9-4dbc-bb1f-d9d4620d1704-image.png\" style=\"width: 292px; height: 70px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ba3b809c-dcb6-4702-8655-8c01de014fbc-image.png\" style=\"width: 270px; height: 80px;\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Diisobutylaluminium hydride, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AlH</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>Bu</mi><msub><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;also known as DIBAL or DIBAL-H, is an exceedingly useful and versatile reducing agent. It is an electrophilic reducing agent, usually employed in selective reductions of esters or nitriles to aldehydes</p><p>So, in first step nitrile group will be reduced to aldehyde group.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c28ff58c-e447-4e6f-acf7-c45ba8d86919-image.png\" style=\"width: 513px; height: 170px;\" /></p><p>In second step cross aldol condensation reaction will take place which will give mixture of products. Out of which one of the product will be option B.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27176,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Trichloromethanol","2, 2, 2-Trichloropropanol","Chloroform","2, 2, 2-Trichloroethanol"],"answer":3,"solution":"$2 \\mathrm{CCl}_3 \\mathrm{CHO} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{OH}^{(-)}}{\\longrightarrow} \\mathrm{CCl}_3 \\mathrm{COONa}+\\mathrm{CCl}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$\nCannizaro reaction is a disproportionation reaction\nOne aldehyde molecule is oxidized to salt of the carboxylic Acid, other one is reduced to Alcohol. So the compound is $\\mathrm{CCl}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}$\nIUPAC Name is $2,2,2,-$ Trichloro ethanol","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2011","image":null},{"id":27175,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{NH}_2 \\mathrm{NH}_2, \\stackrel{(-)}{\\mathrm{OH}}$","$\\mathrm{Zn}-\\mathrm{Hg} / \\mathrm{HCl}$","$\\mathrm{Na}$, Liq. $\\mathrm{NH}_3$","$\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{ZnHg} / \\mathrm{HCl}$ can't be used due to the presence of acid sensitive group i.e. $\\mathrm{OH}$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/G829JQPIFEsuve3PcLMSf1h86G7FHuPwPxCm-5FBNOI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nand $\\mathrm{Na} / \\mathrm{Liq} . \\mathrm{NH}_3$ and $\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$ convert $-\\mathrm{CO}-$ into $-\\mathrm{CH}(\\mathrm{OH})-$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":27141,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/991df1c2-2c66-4247-88c6-43f950a78ebb-image6.png\" style=\"width: 134px; height: 100px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/347d4551-2690-4cb6-8dec-86ec2aeae8d8-image7.png\" style=\"width: 130px; height: 150px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed8041f7-668e-4f67-9ae8-586d3ac8ae5f-image8.png\" style=\"width: 147px; height: 100px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b2673fa2-ec0f-42d0-86c5-82be2463e6f8-image9.png\" style=\"width: 143px; height: 150px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Given reaction is a case of intramolecular aldol condensation</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/92380849-16e0-4958-9b2b-a2b00326d0a9-image.png\" style=\"width: 486px; height: 358px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27023,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["2-Methylpent-2-enal","Pent-2-enal","2-Methylbut-2-enal","3-Methylbut-2-enal"],"answer":3,"solution":"Product $x$ is obtained by the Stephen reduction of propanenitrile ($CH_3CH_2CN$).<br>$CH_3CH_2CN \\xrightarrow{SnCl_2/HCl} CH_3CH_2CH=NH \\xrightarrow{H_2O} CH_3CH_2CHO$ (Propanal).<br>Product $y$ is obtained by the reductive ozonolysis of but-2-ene ($CH_3CH=CHCH_3$).<br>$CH_3CH=CHCH_3 \\xrightarrow{O_3, H_2O/Zn} 2CH_3CHO$ (Ethanal).<br>When propanal ($x$) and ethanal ($y$) react in the presence of alkali followed by heating, they undergo cross-aldol condensation.<br>Possible products are:<br>1. Self-aldol of propanal: $CH_3CH_2CHO + CH_3CH_2CHO \\rightarrow CH_3CH_2CH=C(CH_3)CHO$ (2-Methylpent-2-enal).<br>2. Self-aldol of ethanal: $CH_3CHO + CH_3CHO \\rightarrow CH_3CH=CHCHO$ (But-2-enal).<br>3. Cross-aldol (Ethanal as nucleophile): $CH_3CH_2CHO + CH_3CHO \\rightarrow CH_3CH_2CH=CHCHO$ (Pent-2-enal).<br>4. Cross-aldol (Propanal as nucleophile): $CH_3CHO + CH_3CH_2CHO \\rightarrow CH_3CH=C(CH_3)CHO$ (2-Methylbut-2-enal).<br>Comparing with the options, 3-Methylbut-2-enal is not formed in any of these reactions.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27051,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Ex1FBNoJ0qh0IThNQoSXSJZMOYHIG3rJSHY6WAkQ--s.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/GwEUOu-Yfwl7MoA7Wuo6EZRhJx82emhli4jKu4gp26w.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6QQejT0lYD-id_oLYJamM26tP_mcVTIy0KBo6GUre8s.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Kfbnp-ksf8u2d8lsxnkW0HpeuQDSqIJuZgFoiAQ0pTw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/HStrZTIYB-yZZp7EVyoAXb8Cf6LFU4AHHaCLt03XLZA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27052,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Claisen Schmidt reaction\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/904Eet2BXkNsWF2K4wAx5xW0Jz0KCqguPB-dQ3m4Kf8.original.fullsize.png\"><br />mw of benzaldehyde $=106$\n$106 \\times 3=318 \\mathrm{gm}$. Benzaldehyde is required to give 1.5 mole (or $351 \\mathrm{gm}$ ) product","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27149,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"87\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/310afcce-10be-43ec-940c-00db18cfc1c8-image.png\" width=\"230\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"80\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9641280b-a179-46b6-b158-2f20a8f66a8f-image.png\" width=\"231\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"135\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/07f4b3a5-7bb4-4867-b1ec-306d1ee57b23-image.png\" width=\"162\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"133\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c966cc3a-2791-430f-9b63-1cb26916572b-image.png\" width=\"163\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/eff8b53f-bb86-4d23-bf6a-225d6620601c-1559375a-bf8a-436d-9c12-e6012da49d3c-image.png\" style=\"width: 556px; height: 138px;\" /><br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Intramolecular aldol condensation<br /><br /><img height=\"380\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f833ea55-0915-48e6-a840-7a69054bd46f-image.png\" width=\"273\" /><br /><br /><img height=\"400\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4469dfc4-1a1c-4284-babc-c136b2620c0d-image.png\" width=\"259\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27015,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Benzene reacts with $CO$ and $HCl$ in the presence of $CuCl$ to give benzaldehyde ($x$) via the Gattermann-Koch reaction.<br><br>Benzene reacts with ethanoyl chloride ($CH_3COCl$) in the presence of anhydrous $AlCl_3$ to give acetophenone ($y$) via Friedel-Crafts acylation.<br><br>Heating benzaldehyde ($x$) and acetophenone ($y$) in the presence of alkali results in a crossed aldol condensation to form benzalacetophenone ($z$).<br><br>$C_6H_5CHO + CH_3COC_6H_5 \\xrightarrow{OH^-, \\Delta} C_6H_5-CH=CH-CO-C_6H_5 + H_2O$<br><br>The structure of $z$ ($C_6H_5-CH=CH-CO-C_6H_5$) contains two phenyl rings ($6$ $\\pi$ bonds), one $C=C$ double bond ($1$ $\\pi$ bond), and one $C=O$ double bond ($1$ $\\pi$ bond).<br><br>Total number of $\\pi$ bonds = $6 + 1 + 1 = 8$<br><br>Total number of $\\pi$ electrons = $8 \\times 2 = 16$<br><br>Answer: $16$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (08 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27060,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/247cf632-875e-4c2c-ba49-a3c9cbd6608e.png\" style=\"width: 315px; height: 185px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ebf5247a-0d4f-4c84-9b7f-70eb808c531f.png\" style=\"width: 401px; height: 180px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/be766da0-d965-496e-a925-6e58e5db6ddf.png\" style=\"width: 351px; height: 158px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/12114879-7dfb-44a0-a97e-210fd170e723.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 182px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Meta–chlorobenzaldehyde will undergo Cannizzaro reaction with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo><mo> </mo><mi>KOH</mi></math> to give mchlorobenzoate ion and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzyl alcohol. </p><p>Since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzaldehyde does not contain α hydrogen thus with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo><mo> </mo><mi>KOH</mi></math> it undergoes the Cannizzaro reaction. The Cannizzaro reaction for the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzaldehyde is given as:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/50073db2-f5e4-463e-adf9-af7f4a4d5472.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 156px;\"/>Since it is a disproportionation reaction so one molecule of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzaldehyde is reduced to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzyl alcohol at the cost of others which is oxidized potassium <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>-</mo></math>chlorobenzoate.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27016,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["2-Methylpent-4-en-3-one","4-Methylpent-3-en-2-one","4-Methylpent-1-ene","2-Methylpent-3-one"],"answer":1,"solution":"Hydrolysis of prop-1-yne in the presence of $HgSO_4$ and dilute $H_2SO_4$ yields acetone.<br><br>$CH_3-C \\equiv CH + H_2O \\xrightarrow{Hg^{2+}, H^+} CH_3-CO-CH_3$<br><br>Thus, $x$ is acetone.<br><br>Reaction of ethane nitrile ($CH_3CN$) with methyl magnesium bromide ($CH_3MgBr$) followed by hydrolysis also yields acetone.<br><br>$CH_3-C \\equiv N + CH_3MgBr \\rightarrow CH_3-C(CH_3)=NMgBr \\xrightarrow{H_3O^+} CH_3-CO-CH_3$<br><br>Thus, $y$ is acetone.<br><br>Reaction of $x$ and $y$ (both acetone) in the presence of $Ba(OH)_2$ followed by heating results in an aldol condensation.<br><br>$2 CH_3-CO-CH_3 \\xrightarrow{Ba(OH)_2} CH_3-C(OH)(CH_3)-CH_2-CO-CH_3$<br><br>Heating causes dehydration to form an unsaturated ketone.<br><br>$CH_3-C(OH)(CH_3)-CH_2-CO-CH_3 \\xrightarrow{\\Delta} CH_3-C(CH_3)=CH-CO-CH_3$<br><br>Numbering the principal carbon chain to give the lowest locant to the ketone group, the IUPAC name of the product is 4-methylpent-3-en-2-one.<br><br>Answer: 4-Methylpent-3-en-2-one","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27095,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dacfb354-d5fd-4c04-98f7-f90820f88c93-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 140px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bf4940b9-5cd3-478f-91c8-56f017290290-image.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 89px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/125f0614-4ee7-48ae-ba9e-00b336f9238e-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 167px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/79f70513-9fb9-44ba-895f-f93aa2e219e4-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 135px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>In the first step formaldehyde undergoes cross aldol reaction with isobutyraldehyde&nbsp;to form&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>(</strong><strong>A)</strong>and then the product(A)&nbsp;forms cyanohydrin&nbsp;(B)with KCN, which on hydrolysis forms a compound containing&nbsp;carboxylic acid group and finally this molecule undergoes intramolecular esterification to form (C) a stable compound.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0879d387-d640-4ef6-8e79-7bd40ce84413-image.png\" style=\"width: 560px; height: 368px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27163,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/39b33271-3e67-490f-aa65-28b8dab68b7d-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 73px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>This reaction is aldol condensation.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/79164ed3-657f-4956-9ca2-eab5c87f5b48-image.png\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 151px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (11 Apr Online)","image":null}]